      "writtenOn": "2020-04-07T11:06:16Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I have come to dislike packages named \"types\" (others [1] agree). It lends themselves to becoming a monolithic package where everything goes.\n\nMy concrete suggestion is to move this file into a file machine/go/(state/)?machine/types.go; (package name is machine) Then your types below will be (including rename suggestions from below)\nmachine.SwarmingState\nmachine.SwarmingDimensions\nmachine.Mode (or machine.Status)\nmachine.Description\nmachine.UpdateEventType\nmachine.UpdateEvent\n\nVariables:\nmachine.Available\nmachine.Maintenance\nmachine.DimensionsUpdated\nmachine.StateUpdated\n\nI found this to be a useful/readable structure in my Niagara prototype https://skia-review.googlesource.com/c/buildbot/+/268160/14/niagara/go/machine/types.go\n\n[1] https://github.com/golang/go/wiki/CodeReviewComments#package-names",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 1,
        "startChar": 0,
        "endLine": 1,
        "endChar": 13
      },
      "revId": "9bea01bb7d159c921f28e804de4aa17802c9ed22",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": true
    },
