      "message": "Cribbing an idea from the Niagara prototype, what do you think about parsing/processing the raw state from swarming into an actual typed object?\n\nAs a (very bare) example, look at Description https://skia-review.googlesource.com/c/buildbot/+/268160/14/niagara/go/machine/types.go#16\n\nIt has the dimensions and the machine uptime (which had been read out of state); the goal was to have other fields of interest, i.e. temperature, disk space, etc",
      "range": {
